Note:
Haskell Lexer - Complete tokenization for Haskell language

This file provides comprehensive lexical analysis for the Haskell programming
language, including all keywords, operators, literals, identifiers, and
special syntax for pure functional programming constructs.

Haskell Features Covered:
- Keywords (data, type, class, instance, where, let, in, case, of, if, then, else, etc.)
- Operators (function application, composition, arithmetic, logical, etc.)
- Identifiers (variables, constructors, modules, qualified names)
- Literals (integers, floats, characters, strings, list comprehensions)
- Special syntax (layout-sensitive parsing, lambda expressions, type signatures)
- Comments (single-line and multi-line)
- Indentation and layout rules
- Type constructors and type variables
- Pattern matching syntax
- Module system (imports, exports, qualified names)

Dependencies:
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Token Type Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Keywords
Constant TOKEN_DATA as Integer is 1001        Note: data
Constant TOKEN_TYPE as Integer is 1002        Note: type
Constant TOKEN_NEWTYPE as Integer is 1003     Note: newtype
Constant TOKEN_CLASS as Integer is 1004       Note: class
Constant TOKEN_INSTANCE as Integer is 1005    Note: instance
Constant TOKEN_WHERE as Integer is 1006       Note: where
Constant TOKEN_LET as Integer is 1007         Note: let
Constant TOKEN_IN as Integer is 1008          Note: in
Constant TOKEN_CASE as Integer is 1009        Note: case
Constant TOKEN_OF as Integer is 1010          Note: of
Constant TOKEN_IF as Integer is 1011          Note: if
Constant TOKEN_THEN as Integer is 1012        Note: then
Constant TOKEN_ELSE as Integer is 1013        Note: else
Constant TOKEN_MODULE as Integer is 1014      Note: module
